# Ralph operator manual · shard {{SHARD_ID}} ({{BATCH_RANGE}}, {{N_TASKS}} tasks)

> **Generated by `scripts_4x/render_shards.py` from
> `scripts_4x/PROMPT.md.tmpl` into `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/PROMPT.md`.**
> **Do not edit `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/PROMPT.md` directly** — modify the template
> and re-run `render_shards.py --refresh-template-only` to regenerate.
>
> This file is fed via stdin to `claude --print` by `ralph.sh --shard-root
> {{SHARD_ROOT}}`. You — the operator agent — get this prompt plus access
> to the working tree plus a write-boundary `PreToolUse` hook
> (`scripts_4x/hooks/deny_outside_shard.py`, activated by
> `RALPH_SHARD_ROOT={{SHARD_ROOT}}`). Complete one locked story, then exit
> so the harness can proceed to the next iteration.

---

## §0. What the harness already did before launching you

- Asserted the working branch matches `prd.json[branchName]`; otherwise FATAL.
- Picked the first `passes=false` story in `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/prd.json` and
  wrote `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/current_story.json` (`{"id": "<STORY_ID>"}`).
- Acquired the per-shard instance lock at `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/.instance`.
- Snapshotted every story's `passes` value before this iteration. If any
  unrelated story's `passes` flips during your work, this iteration is
  treated as VIOLATION and the harness self-heals the prd.
- Exported `RALPH_SHARD_ROOT={{SHARD_ROOT}}` so the PreToolUse hook denies
  any write outside this shard, plus any write to `*.py` files.

You may only modify the **locked story**. All other stories' `passes`
fields are off-limits.

This shard owns {{N_BATCHES}} stories (`{{BATCH_RANGE}}`, total {{N_TASKS}}
tasks). The acceptance gate is whatever `prd.json` configures per story —
see `.ralph/scripts/acceptance.py` for the plug-in interface
(`jsonl_schema` / `command` / `composite`).

---

## §1. Read these files first

1. `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/current_story.json` → take `id` (call it `${LOCKED_ID}`)
2. `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/progress.txt` `## Codebase Patterns` block — this is the
   conventions SoT, do not contradict it.
3. `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/prd.json` → find the story with `id == ${LOCKED_ID}`. Note
   its `acceptanceGate` (or fall back to `acceptance.default_gate`),
   `entryCount`, `modifies`, `creates`, and `acceptanceCriteria`.
4. `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/stories/manifest.json` → find `batches[].story_id ==
   ${LOCKED_ID}`. Take `input_file` (a symlink to baseline batch input) and
   `task_ids` (the expected verdict id set, length == `entryCount`).
5. Read `${input_file}` — the per-task input data.

For code-implementation stories (`acceptanceGate.type == "command"`), steps
3–5 collapse to "read what files to edit and what test command to run".

---

## §2. Resume previous progress (deduplication)

For data-fill stories that stream verdicts:
`{{SHARD_ROOT}}/state/seen_task_ids.json` is the union of already-handled
task ids. Skip rows whose id is in that file — `pending = batch_input \
seen_task_ids` is what this iteration must process.

If `pending` is empty (the whole batch is already in seen), skip to §4
validation directly.

For code stories, this section does not apply — there is no per-task seen
state.

---

## §3. Do the work (subagent dispatch for data-fill, direct edit for code)

### 3.1 Data-fill (`acceptanceGate.type == "jsonl_schema"`)

Use `.ralph/scripts/run_batch.py` (shard mode adds `--shard-root
{{SHARD_ROOT}}`).

```bash
uv run python .ralph/scripts/run_batch.py --shard-root {{SHARD_ROOT}} prepare
```

This:
- reads `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/current_story.json`,
- computes `pending = batch_input \ seen_task_ids`,
- writes a subagent prompt to `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/state/subagent_prompt.md`
  (using either the default streaming-verdict template or one supplied via
  `--prompt-template`),
- emits a JSON summary including `n_pending`, `subagent_prompt_path`,
  `schema_version`,
- auto-recovers when `attempts > 0` and the entire batch is already in
  `seen` (clears the batch's verdicts + seen entries, redoes them).

Then dispatch the subagent:

```
Agent({
  description: "verdict pass {{SHARD_ID}}/${LOCKED_ID}",
  subagent_type: "general-purpose",
  prompt: <full text of {{SHARD_ROOT}}/state/subagent_prompt.md>,
})
```

The subagent appends one verdict at a time using
`.ralph/scripts/append_verdict.py` (the helper enforces schema +
schema_version + reason length, fsyncs each row, and atomically updates
`seen_task_ids.json`). All writes are confined by the PreToolUse hook to
`{{SHARD_ROOT}}/`.

### 3.2 Code-implementation (`acceptanceGate.type == "command"`)

Edit only the files listed in the locked story's `modifies` / `creates`.
Do **not** touch other shards or the baseline. Run the configured command
(e.g. `pytest tests/test_<x>.py`) to confirm it passes locally before
proceeding to §4.

### 3.3 Subagents are sandboxed by the hook

The hook will deny any write outside `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/` (and any `*.py`
modification by a subagent). Trust the boundary; do not attempt
workarounds.

---

## §4. Run the gate, finalize, emit promise token

```bash
uv run python .ralph/scripts/run_batch.py --shard-root {{SHARD_ROOT}} validate
```
(For pure code stories you can replace this with `pytest` directly. The
gate plug-in's CommandGate runs the same command and reports the same
PASS/FAIL.)

Then, regardless of validate exit code:

```bash
uv run python .ralph/scripts/run_batch.py --shard-root {{SHARD_ROOT}} finalize
```

`finalize` runs the same gate, then:

- **PASS**: flip `prd.json[id == ${LOCKED_ID}].passes = true`, append to
  progress.txt, emit `<promise>YIELD</promise>` (or
  `<promise>COMPLETE</promise>` if all stories now pass).
- **FAIL** (attempt < max_attempts): increment `attempts`, log a blocker,
  emit `<promise>YIELD</promise>` so the harness retries the same story.
- **FAIL** (attempt ≥ max_attempts): emit
  `VIOLATION: ${LOCKED_ID} ...` and exit 2 (harness circuit-breaker
  takes over).

Copy the promise token verbatim to your final stdout — the harness greps
for it.

---

## §5. Completion integrity (anti-cheat)

`<promise>COMPLETE</promise>` declares that **every** story in
`{{SHARD_ROOT}}/prd.json` has `passes = true`. `run_batch.py finalize`
already cross-validates this against the prd.

> Note: this shard's COMPLETE only means *this shard* finished its
> {{COMPLETE_THRESHOLD}} stories. Sibling shards are still running until
> they emit their own COMPLETE; the merge step
> (`scripts_4x/merge_shards.py`) only runs after all shards finish.

**Do not output a false promise** to escape the loop. `ralph.sh` re-checks
the prd before honoring COMPLETE; lying produces a log entry and the loop
continues.

If you are blocked and cannot make progress this iteration:

1. Append the blocker to `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/progress.txt` `## Current Blockers`.
2. Emit `<promise>YIELD</promise>` so the harness retries.
3. Let `attempts` accumulate to `max_attempts` so finalize routes through
   VIOLATION naturally.

---

## §6. Red lines (instant VIOLATION)

The PreToolUse hook enforces most of these at the tool layer:

### Inputs / completed artifacts

- Any path under `eval_results/` (red-line: hook deny).
- Any path under `data_processing/gold_fixtures/` (or your project's
  equivalent input SoT).
- Any path under `docs/` (plan / spec SoT).

### Harness sources

- `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/PROMPT.md` (this file — regenerated from template).
- `ralph.sh` (operator must not self-modify the harness).
- `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/progress.txt` `## Codebase Patterns` block (operator may
  only append `## Completed Stories` and `## Current Blockers`).
- `.ralph/scripts/run_batch.py` / `.ralph/scripts/append_verdict.py` /
  `.ralph/scripts/acceptance.py` (schema validators; hook denies any `*.py`
  write).
- `.ralph/` (single-process baseline, owned by the main session).
- Other `.ralph-shard-*/` directories (cross-shard contamination).
- `.ralph/stories/batch-*.jsonl` / `.ralph/stories/manifest.json` (slice
  source of truth; this shard references via symlink only).

### Git operations

- No `git push`, `git rebase`, `git reset --hard`, `git commit --amend`,
  or `git checkout` of another branch.
- Subagents must not `git commit` — only the main session commits.
- Subagents must not write `prd.json` / `progress.txt`. Only the main
  session does, via `run_batch.py finalize`.

### Data-fill specific

- Every batch must dispatch a fresh subagent (serial 1×N).
- Subagents must streaming-write each verdict (the helper enforces this).
- `schema_version` must equal the value configured in
  `prd.acceptance.default_gate.schema_version`.

---

## §7. Final stdout contract

Your final stdout (the line the harness greps) must contain exactly one
of:

- `<promise>YIELD</promise>`
- `<promise>COMPLETE</promise>`
- `VIOLATION: <reason>`

Anything else (intermediate `prepare` / `validate` JSON, subagent
transcripts, etc.) is fine; the harness only looks at the trailing token.

When you stop, the harness will: clear `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/current_story.json`,
run a structural diff (shard-aware: only inspects `{{SHARD_ROOT}}/`
changes), cool down 10s, then begin the next iteration.

